  "prompt": "What are some best songs to listen to?",
  "response": "The best songs to listen to can vary greatly depending on your taste and mood, but here are some popular and critically acclaimed tracks from various genres and eras that you might enjoy:\n\n### Pop\n1. **\"Blinding Lights\" by The Weeknd** - A retro-inspired track with a modern twist.\n2. **\"Watermelon Sugar\" by Harry Styles** - A feel-good, summery anthem.\n3. **\"Levitating\" by Dua Lipa feat. DaBaby** - A catchy dance-pop tune.\n\n### Rock\n1. **\"Bohemian Rhapsody\" by Queen** - A timeless classic with a unique structure.\n2. **\"Stairway to Heaven\" by Led Zeppelin** - Known for its intricate guitar work and epic progression.\n3. **\"Smells Like Teen Spirit\" by Nirvana** - A defining grunge anthem.\n\n### Hip-Hop/Rap\n1. **\"Sicko Mode\" by Travis Scott** - An experimental and multi-segmented hit.\n2. **\"God's Plan\" by Drake** - Popular for its catchy beat and motivational lyrics.\n3. **\"Alright\" by Kendrick Lamar** - An empowering track with strong social commentary.\n\n### R&B/Soul\n1. **\"Superstition\" by Stevie Wonder** - A classic with a funky groove.\n2. **\"Adore You\" by Harry Styles** - A modern take on a soulful style.\n3. **\"Rolling in the Deep\" by Adele** - Powerful vocals and an intense melody.\n\n### Electronic/Dance\n1. **\"Titanium\" by David Guetta feat. Sia** - An empowering anthem with strong vocals.\n2. **\"Strobe\" by deadmau5** - Known for its progressive buildup.\n3. **\"Get Lucky\" by Daft Punk feat. Pharrell Williams** - Funky and upbeat.\n\n### Indie/Alternative\n1. **\"Take Me Out\" by Franz Ferdinand** - A high-energy rock track.\n2. **\"Dog Days Are Over\" by Florence + The Machine** - Uplifting and anthemic.\n3. **\"Heroes\" by David Bowie** - An iconic song of hope and resilience.\n\n### Jazz/Classical\n1. **\"Take Five\" by Dave Brubeck** - A classic piece with a unique time signature.\n2. **\"Clair de Lune\" by Claude Debussy** - A beautiful and serene piano composition.\n3. **\"So What\" by Miles Davis** - A cornerstone of modal jazz.\n\nThese are just a starting point, and exploring different artists and genres will help you discover even more great music that suits your personal preferences. Enjoy your listening journey!",
